@whot do you remember where in the code we create the resolutions (set the defaults)?

drivers are supposed to call ratbag_resolution_set_dpi_list() or ratbag_resolution_set_dpi_list_from_range()

No. A report rate of 0Hz will never be written to anywhere. Bellow we have
if (rate_hz) {
	log_debug(ratbag, "report rate is %u\n", rate_hz);
	ratbag_device_for_each_profile(device, profile)
		profile->hz = rate_hz;
} 
if (rate_hz) is the same as if (rate_hz != 0). We set the rate_hz to 0 if no valid report rate is found and then only act on valid values.

