@thesecretmaster Its not hard just takes some setup. You need to have windows or a windows VM to work with. In Windows you install Wireshark and USBpcap. Once you do that, you install Roccat software, load up wireshark, find the mouse and then just look at packets. I usually change a setting in roccat, save it, and see what packets are sent. The tricky part is there is constant spam from the mouse for movement/laser positioning stuff. Its easy to filter if you set a query for a size minimum of the packet. Then you just need to figure out the structure and what does what in the packet. Not hard but very time consuming.

